{"cursor":"4399","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Door-to-door' is a sales technique in which a salesperson walks from the door\nof one house to the door of another trying to sell a product or service to the\ngeneral public. A variant of this involves cold calling first, when another\nsales representative attempts to gain agreement that a salesperson should visit.\nDoor-to-door selling is usually conducted in the mid afternoon, when the\nmajority of people are at home.\n","linknr":294,"url":"Door-to-door","recorded":1362559933,"links":27,"instances":["trade"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Business","Personal selling"],"headings":["The model","Banning","Door-to-door shipping","Door to doorers","Religious work","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Crystal_kchart.png/25px-Crystal_kchart.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["hawker","trade"]],"members":["hawker"],"related":["Sales","Cold_calling","Discount_store","Siding","Business_model","Direct_marketing","Information_Age","Coupon","Season_ticket","Pay_television","Broadband_Internet_access","Telecommunications","Verizon_Communications","Verizon_FiOS","Cable_television","Cable_Internet","AT&T","U-verse","Account_executive","Encyclopedia","United_States","Green_River_Ordinance","International","Jurisdiction","Customs","Import_taxes","Jehovah's_witnesses","Mormons","Begging","Canvassing","Hawker_(trade)","Peddler","Solicitation"]}